[SN]TITLE[SN]
Pedestrian dies in Crawley car crash

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A pedestrian has died after he was hit by a car in West Sussex.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 30-year-old man was pronounced dead on the A23, near the K2 Leisure Centre, in Crawley on Friday.
The driver of the car was taken to hospital with minor injuries, Sussex Police said.
The crash happened on Pease Pottage Hill, at the junction with Tilgate Drive. An air ambulance also attended and the road was closed for several hours.
